# Workaround

I extended @Alexandre-Casetta 's solution to support primitive arrays and optional properties:
```ts
export type Exact<TKnown, T extends TKnown> = {
  [Key in keyof T]: Key extends keyof TKnown
    ? T[Key] extends unknown[]
      ? Exclude<T[Key], undefined>
      : T[Key] extends object
        ? Exact<Exclude<TKnown[Key], undefined>, Exclude<T[Key], undefined>>
        : Exclude<T[Key], undefined>
    : never;
};

function foo<T extends Something>(t: Exact<Something, T>) { return t; }
```
But before you get too excited the newly inferred ReturnType is not compatible with the old unsafe function, so If you would like to use it like this:
```ts
function fooUnsafe<T extends Something>(t: T) { return t; }
function foo<T extends Something>(t: Exact<Something, T>) { 
  fooUnsafe(t) // !!! type error :( 
}
```

I use it anyways, still **better than being unsafe**.

